item.title: Serena Williams argument with umpire 2011 US OPEN Final but Avoids Ban
item.description:
Serena Williams argument with umpire 2011 US OPEN Final but Avoids Ban
WAS THE PENALTY FAIR? PLEASE COMMENT YOUR OPINION!!! Serena Williams outburst at the US Open 2011 final. She gets fined $2000 but escapes ban. Williams blames her outburst on Emotions..Was the umpire Eva Asderaki correct to give the point to Stosur? Was there any difference between the noise Serena made and a mega loud grunting sound made by many other Women on the tour? If she had made such a sound when her opponent was about to put away an easy ball then maybe a point penalty against her would have been fair, but surely the umpire should be able to apply rules to the situation, and if that was done there is no way the point should have been give to Stosur. Regardless, maybe this would not have effected the result. What do you think?
